25#include <sys/cdefs.h>
26__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_bios_shadowacpi.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");

28#include "priv.h"
29
30#if defined(CONFIG_ACPI) && defined(CONFIG_X86)
31int nouveau_acpi_get_bios_chunk(uint8_t *bios, int offset, int len);
32bool nouveau_acpi_rom_supported(struct device *);
33#else
34static inline bool
35nouveau_acpi_rom_supported(struct device *dev)
36{
37 return false;
38}
39
40static inline int
41nouveau_acpi_get_bios_chunk(uint8_t *bios, int offset, int len)
42{
43 return -EINVAL;
44}
45#endif
46
47/* This version of the shadow function disobeys the ACPI spec and tries
48 * to fetch in units of more than 4KiB at a time. This is a LOT faster
49 * on some systems, such as Lenovo W530.
50 */
51static u32
52acpi_read_fast(void *data, u32 offset, u32 length, struct nvkm_bios *bios)
53{
54 u32 limit = (offset + length + 0xfff) & ~0xfff;
55 u32 start = offset & ~0x00000fff;
56 u32 fetch = limit - start;
57
58 if (nvbios_extend(bios, limit) >= 0) {
59 int ret = nouveau_acpi_get_bios_chunk(bios->data, start, fetch);
60 if (ret == fetch)
61 return fetch;
62 }
63
64 return 0;
65}
66
67/* Other systems, such as the one in fdo#55948, will report a success
68 * but only return 4KiB of data. The common bios fetching logic will
69 * detect an invalid image, and fall back to this version of the read
70 * function.
71 */
72static u32
73acpi_read_slow(void *data, u32 offset, u32 length, struct nvkm_bios *bios)
74{
75 u32 limit = (offset + length + 0xfff) & ~0xfff;
76 u32 start = offset & ~0xfff;
77 u32 fetch = 0;
78
79 if (nvbios_extend(bios, limit) >= 0) {
80 while (start + fetch < limit) {
81 int ret = nouveau_acpi_get_bios_chunk(bios->data,
82 start + fetch,
83 0x1000);
84 if (ret != 0x1000)
85 break;
86 fetch += 0x1000;
87 }
88 }
89
90 return fetch;
91}
92
93static void *
94acpi_init(struct nvkm_bios *bios, const char *name)
95{
96 if (!nouveau_acpi_rom_supported(bios->subdev.device->dev))
97 return ERR_PTR(-ENODEV);
98 return NULL;
99}
100
101const struct nvbios_source
102nvbios_acpi_fast = {
103 .name = "ACPI",
104 .init = acpi_init,
105 .read = acpi_read_fast,
106 .rw = false,
107 .require_checksum = true,
108};
109
110const struct nvbios_source
111nvbios_acpi_slow = {
112 .name = "ACPI",
113 .init = acpi_init,
114 .read = acpi_read_slow,
115 .rw = false,
116};
